snippet.title: Woman taken to hospital after car flipped
snippet.content: A WOMAN was taken to hospital for treatment after her car flipped onto it's roof after hitting a curb then tree in Innaloo. The incident happened before 3pm on Barnes Street. A WA Police spokeswoman said the female driver was driving along the street when it hit a curb then collided into a tree and rolled. The tree then fell onto the car. The woman was then taken to Sir Charles Gairdner Hospital.
